sections.Trivia:
- The police car from The High School Girl Trio's Secret Café reappeared.
- The restaurant fanchised Welcome Burger, named after McDonalds', which appeared in Clash of Red and Black, reappears in this case.
- The movie in the beginning shows the Azengers, a group of heroes that are actually inspired by Marvel Comics' Avengers. The movie shows Kamen Yaiba joining the group.
- While the game console the Detective Boys were playing weren't shown, the controllers are heavily resemble the Joy-Con of Nintendo Switch. The game they were playing also heavily resembles Puyo Puyo Tetris, though this was made much less obvious in the anime.
- The film production staff's van is a white Toyota HiAce. The license plate number is 新宿 330, ふ 59-65 (Shinjuku 330, Fu 59-65).
- The car that rammed Jinmei in the past is a white hardtop Mercedes CLK320. The license plate number is 新宿 320, ま 23-06 (Shinjuku 320, Ma 23-06).
- Daisaku Odori wears Nike sneakers.
- The ambulance that carried Odori's corpse is a Toyota HiMedic. The license plate number is 新宿 800, ひ 47-62 (Shinjuku 800, Hi 47-62).
- The names of the suspects come from Japanese Detective drama series[1]:
- Shigematsu Tomioka (富岡 茂松) comes from Uwasa no Keiji Tommy to Matsu (噂の刑事トミーとマツ) character Tomio Okano (岡野 富夫) and actor Shigeru Matsuzaki (松崎 しげる), who played in the show;
- Daisaku Odori (尾取 大策) comes from Bayside Shakedown (踊る大捜査線), in Japanese Odoru Daisōsasen;
- Saiya Tokuzono (徳薗 彩也) comes from Tokusō Saizensen (特捜最前線);
- Nanako Jinmei (神明 奈々子) comes from G-Men '75 (Gメン'75), in Japanese Jīmen' nanajūgo;
- Yota Hoegi (吠木 曜太) comes from Taiyō ni Hoero! (太陽にほえろ！);
- Hideka Aburai (油井 英香) comes from Abunai Deka (あぶない刑事);
- Nishibe (西部) comes from Seibu Keisatsu (西部警察);
- The TV show they are producing, Detective 48 (刑事48) comes from the TV show Keiji Shichijin (刑事7人) and idol group AKB 48.
